  "texts": [
    "Additionally, we conducted SFT experiments on LLMs of varying sizes using UrbanPlanText and subsequently evaluated their performance on UrbanPlanBench.",
    "Aligning with previous benchmarking experiments, we still employed the Qwen1.5 model across a spectrum of parameter sizes ranging from 0.8B to 32B.",
    "We illustrated their post-SFT performance in Figure 4.",
    "Similar to previous observations, we can observe a clear scaling effect on the accuracy of MCQ-S questions, with larger models demonstrating substantially improved performance compared to their smaller counterparts.",
    "Particularly, we noted that SFT yielded more substantial benefits for smaller models."
